\begin_layout Standard
In traditional societies with strong prominence of societal rules and customs,
 often women are not seen as the best fit for businesses like agro-input
 dealing.
 Uganda is no different from such societies and Ugandan women are mostly
 expected to be engaged in household chores and cater to the daily needs
 of the family.
 Although the ideas of independent earning ventures and modern agricultural
 technology adoptions for women are becoming widespread, government intervention
s and trainings by non-governmental institutions 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
